metadata.name: Putin In Sight
metadata.description:
now let us pause for a moment to consider the deeper meaning of this work.. ok that's long enough. 

this effect is achieved by applying mod podge onto a wood panel, then subsequently pressing an image onto the surface, leaving behind an idiosyncratic texture and ink decay.

what exactly is the artist trying to say here?

is this a response to the primal urge to take rudimentary tools and turn them into play things? or perhaps something much more sinister.

are you fucking kidding me?  
who writes this shit?

anyways, you decide. seriously, i have no fucking clue.
